aw is a property of the conformal field theory at the UV fixed point, valid\nfor arbitrary relevant deformations and insensitive to the details of the\nquench protocol. Our results highlight the difference between smooth fast\nquenches and instantaneous quenches where the Hamiltonian abruptly changes at\nsome time.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Nov 2014 21:59:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 5 Mar 2015 23:28:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 4 Oct 2017 12:50:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-05"}
